{"id":"ec08266e-e812-4a50-a310-2b6e29d308b5","userId":"e8f217b2-1fcc-414b-848e-ba2547929ee4","role":"assistant","content":"It sounds like your dad is bringing home a lot of stress and frustration from work, and unfortunately, he's taking it out on you and your family. That can be really tough to deal with, especially when you feel like you're being targeted for no reason.\n\nIt's like, you're just trying to live your life and be yourself, and then suddenly your dad comes home and unleashes all this anger and frustration on you. It's not fair, and it's not okay. You deserve to feel safe and loved in your own home, not like you're walking on eggshells waiting for the next explosion.\n\nCan you tell me more about what happens when your dad comes home from work? Is it always like this, or are there some days that are better than others? And how do you usually cope with these situations? Do you try to avoid him, or do you stand up for yourself, or is there something else that you do to deal with the stress and anxiety of it all?","createdAt":"2026-05-15T19:27:32.511Z","_id":"LnpjAaQj3BhCt0LG"}
